<glossary>
<definition id="fs-id2137503"><term>acute mountain sickness (AMS)</term> <meaning id="fs-id2109349"> condition that occurs a result of acute exposure to high altitude due to a low partial pressure of oxygen</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id2324966"><term>acclimatization</term> <meaning id="fs-id1989680">process of adjustment that the respiratory system makes due to chronic exposure to high altitudes</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id1479502"><term>hyperpnea</term> <meaning id="fs-id2507754">increased rate and depth of ventilation due to an increase in oxygen demand that does not significantly alter blood oxygen or carbon dioxide levels</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id2009037"><term>hyperventilation</term> <meaning id="fs-id2430274">increased ventilation rate that leads to abnormally low blood carbon dioxide levels and high (alkaline) blood pH</meaning></definition>
</glossary>
